18:18.577 --> 18:26.808
1,000 times, but you would hope that the guy across 
the hall, the room would open their window, and

18:18.577 --> 18:26.808
you'd open your window, and maybe you'd get a 
little breeze. But I was assigned room 423. I

18:30.253 --> 18:32.275
remember that room well. I came back to teach ROTC 
here, and I remember going up to that room, dorm

18:32.356 --> 18:41.107
two, and two sophomores were in the room and went in 
there. And they were doing a biology project, and

18:41.328 --> 18:44.892
they had a fish in the sink. And I just thought that 
was very appropriate. That's Fish Henderson's

18:46.735 --> 18:48.297
room. I got ready to leave, and they said, sir, are 
you going to come back? And I said, well, I might

18:52.847 --> 18:54.929
drop in someday. Why? And he said, they said, well, 
if you are, we're going to change rooms with the

18:55.189 --> 18:58.373
freshmen. So I thought that was kind of humorous. 
