19:03.359 --> 19:05.782
the first semester. Three of them left school 
before the semester was over. I ended up rooming

19:10.568 --> 19:14.453
the rest of my time with another freshman from Big 
Springs who did not have a penny, worked as a

19:14.990 --> 19:20.840
waiter. And later on, he ended up getting his PhD 
and teaching at a junior college. So I think that

19:27.170 --> 19:35.444
set the example of what A&M could do for people that 
were really, we wore the same clothes, ate the same

19:27.170 --> 19:35.444
food. But second semester, we roomed together the 
whole semester. Why did those others leave? I

19:44.751 --> 19:54.148
think the first one left the third week we were 
here, and I think he came from a completely

19:44.751 --> 19:54.148
different background than I did. He came down here 
in a new car and had been a partier, was from down

19:55.110 --> 20:01.281
near Baytown. And he just didn't like the 
structure we had of being a freshman. And you could

20:06.899 --> 20:09.742
call it harassment. Some people referred to it as 
hazing. Maybe another term could be good

20:12.025 --> 20:14.247
training. Another one just was definitely 
homesick. And I had gone to Philmont Scout Ranch

20:19.193 --> 20:21.335
with him. His father had been an assistant 
